column5: What a great weather season - but hunting is slow  Anyone been hunting around Barrie?
Usually by this time of year I see them on the way to work, but this is way too warm, I think they're still on the beach.
Y'all stay out in the Deer woods... more room out on the lake for me!!!!

I was out again last night and saw one but couldn't get a clean shot at it. That is the 4th one I have seen in 5 trips but they are really skittish. They seem to be hanging back in the cedars still, just hasn't been cold enough to get them moving around much.

I've been out a couple times near Bradford,Seen deer almost everytime,got one shot off,which seemed to be low as the blood trail dwindled to nothing,and we found no deer ,that was thursday,I'll be back at her this week....TC.....Chuck.......
Maybe y'all need more practice before you climb a tree..
Who can think about hunting with temps like this. Ah,but it wont be long before it will get cold and nasty.
